## I**nvisible Choices in Overlooked Pathways** (Dissertation)

My three-paper dissertation examines how education policies related to language services and gifted identification are interpreted and enacted, and how these processes shape multilingual studentsâ€™ access to learning opportunities across different institutional contexts.

**Outputs:** Dissertation forthcoming, Conference presentations\
**Methods:** Critical discourse analysis, Thematic analysis, Intersectional modeling (MAIHDA), Regression Models, Document analysis, Quasi-experimental policy analysis (difference-in-differences)
:::

